  "prompt": "What is Inspect Element? How do you read the codes?",
  "response": "\"Inspect Element\" is a web browser developer tool that allows you to view and interact with the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript of a webpage. Here's a detailed explanation:\n\nHow to Access Inspect Element:\n1. Right-click on any part of a webpage\n2. Select \"Inspect\" or \"Inspect Element\"\n3. Keyboard shortcuts:\n   - Windows/Linux: Ctrl + Shift + I\n   - Mac: Cmd + Option + I\n\nKey Sections in Inspect Element:\n\n1. Elements Tab:\n- Shows the HTML structure of the page\n- Allows you to:\n  * View HTML code\n  * Modify HTML in real-time\n  * See applied CSS styles\n  * Inspect element hierarchies\n\n2. Styles Panel:\n- Displays CSS rules applied to selected elements\n- Shows:\n  * Inherited styles\n  * Computed styles\n  * Responsive design properties\n\n3. Console Tab:\n- Displays JavaScript errors\n- Allows running JavaScript commands\n- Helps with debugging\n\n4. Network Tab:\n- Shows resources loaded by webpage\n- Displays loading times\n- Helps analyze network performance\n\nTips for Reading Code:\n- Understand HTML structure\n- Look for class and ID attributes\n- Examine CSS selectors\n- Check JavaScript interactions\n- Use browser's developer tools\n\nCommon Uses:\n- Web development\n- Debugging\n- Learning website structures\n- Temporary styling changes",
